div1.p:
Q. When had you seen the property last? - I cannot exactly say;
Thomas Baynes
my butler can.

Court to Prosecutor. Did you deliver him any goods that Clarke had bought of you? - Yes, but he was discharged by four o'clock in the afternoon; his landlord found the first sheet between his bed and sacking;
John Woodward
is his landlord.

Q. Do you know the prisoner Seville at the bar? - I know him very well;
John Wright
is his real name, as he always told me.
